title: Dang Cold Asian Noodle Salad
summary: Dang Cold Asian Noodle Salad might be just the main course you are searching for. This recipe serves 4 and costs $1.87 per serving. Watching your figure? This dairy free recipe has 550 calories, 17g of protein, and 31g of fat per serving. If you have chili oil, soba noodles, napa cabbage, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the sesame seeds you could follow this main course with the Sesame Banana Bread as a dessert. 1 person found this recipe to be tasty and satisfying. It is brought to you by Foodnetwork. With a spoonacular score of 79%, this dish is pretty good. Similar recipes are Cold Asian Noodle Salad, Cold Asian Noodle Salad, and Cold Asian Noodle Salad [VIDEO].

winePairing.pairingText: Asian on the menu? Try pairing with Riesling, Gewurztraminer, and Chenin Blanc. The best wine for Asian food depends on the cuisine and dish - of course - but these acidic whites pair with a number of traditional meals, spicy or not. You could try Eroica Riesling. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.2 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 24 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Eroica Riesling
productMatches.description: This Eroica shows the crisp acidity of the 2007 vintage, which was the best acidity holding year in the past five years. The wine delivers mandarin orange and sweet lime aromas and flavors with subtle mineral notes. The cooler September, along with selecting fruit from higher elevation and cooler sites, contributed to the mouth-watering acidity balanced by beautiful Washington Riesling fruit.An amazing pairing with sweet, flavorful Dungeness crab.

instructions: Watch how to make this recipe.                    In a medium stock pot, boil water, add salt and cook noodles. When finished, place noodles in an ice water bath to cool. Drain and set aside.                          In a medium bowl combine, sesame oil, vinegar, soy sauce, hot chili oil, hoisin and extra-virgin olive oil. Mix thoroughly and then combine prepared vegetables and noodles.                          Garnish with sesame seeds and peanuts.

steps.step: Watch how to make this recipe.
In a medium stock pot, boil water, add salt and cook noodles. When finished, place noodles in an ice water bath to cool.
In a medium bowl combine, sesame oil, vinegar, soy sauce, hot chili oil, hoisin and extra-virgin olive oil.
Mix thoroughly and then combine prepared vegetables and noodles.
Garnish with sesame seeds and peanuts.
